snippet.textDisplay:
After over 40 years, I'm actually starting to dislike Star Wars. 😱 Instead of a story, these latests films have proven to be nothing more than a multimillion-dollar version of Mad Libs.

While I try never to begrudge anyone what they enjoy, it does make me sad for those actually eating this stuff up ─ including these attempts to justify their imbecilic haphazard decisions.

It's as though we fans are so desperate for content that we continue to lower our standards. Ridiculous things like this make it hard to get others to take science fiction & fantasy seriously. We really should expect more from our genre films, not less.

snippet.textDisplay: I think that the reason that the clone has scars and flaws that would seem to fit with what they would have been if it had been the old body is because the dark side doesn't let you recover from that kind of stuff. It even fits what Yoda said " If once you start down the dark path, forever will it dominate your destiny, consume you it will.". I think that he meant that it will "consume you" physically, spiritually and mentally. In other words there is no way to permanently fix any damage of any type that is done by the dark side. That would also explain why all of the Snoke clones were all messed up, when we have seen that Snoke when he was young didn't naturally look like that. Even Palpatine healing himself by draining the life from others would have been at most a temporary fix, he would have had to have done it more and more and it would have healed him less and less everytime. That is my theory on it at least. What do you think?
